#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:30
msgid ""
"Enables automatic adjustments of the exposure time and/or iris aperture. The "
"effect of manual changes of the exposure time or iris aperture while these "
"features are enabled is undefined, drivers should ignore such requests. "
"Possible values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:42
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_AUTO``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_AUTO``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:43
msgid "Automatic exposure time, automatic iris aperture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:44
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_MANUAL``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_MANUAL``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:45
msgid "Manual exposure time, manual iris."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:46
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_SHUTTER_PRIORITY``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_SHUTTER_PRIORITY``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:47
msgid "Manual exposure time, auto iris."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:48
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_APERTURE_PRIORITY``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_APERTURE_PRIORITY``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:49
msgid "Auto exposure time, manual iris."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:53
msgid "``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_ABSOLUTE (integer)``"
msgstr "``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_ABSOLUTE (integer)``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:54
msgid ""
"Determines the exposure time of the camera sensor. The exposure time is "
"limited by the frame interval. Drivers should interpret the values as 100 Âµs "
"units, where the value 1 stands for 1/10000th of a second, 10000 for 1 "
"second and 100000 for 10 seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:59
msgid "``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_AUTO_PRIORITY (boolean)``"
msgstr "``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_AUTO_PRIORITY (boolean)``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:60
msgid ""
"When ``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_AUTO`` is set to ``AUTO`` or ``APERTURE_PRIORITY``, "
"this control determines if the device may dynamically vary the frame rate. "
"By default this feature is disabled (0) and the frame rate must remain "
"constant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:65
msgid "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_EXPOSURE_BIAS (integer menu)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:66
msgid ""
"Determines the automatic exposure compensation, it is effective only when "
"``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_AUTO`` control is set to ``AUTO``, ``SHUTTER_PRIORITY`` "
"or ``APERTURE_PRIORITY``. It is expressed in terms of EV, drivers should "
"interpret the values as 0.001 EV units, where the value 1000 stands for +1 "
"EV."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:72
msgid ""
"Increasing the exposure compensation value is equivalent to decreasing the "
"exposure value (EV) and will increase the amount of light at the image "
"sensor. The camera performs the exposure compensation by adjusting absolute "
"exposure time and/or aperture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:79
msgid "``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_METERING``"
msgstr "``V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE_METERING``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:82
msgid "enum v4l2_exposure_metering -"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:83
msgid ""
"Determines how the camera measures the amount of light available for the "
"frame exposure. Possible values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:92
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_AVERAGE``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_AVERAGE``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:93
msgid ""
"Use the light information coming from the entire frame and average giving no "
"weighting to any particular portion of the metered area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:95
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_CENTER_WEIGHTED``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_CENTER_WEIGHTED``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:96
msgid ""
"Average the light information coming from the entire frame giving priority "
"to the center of the metered area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:98
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_SPOT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_SPOT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:99
msgid "Measure only very small area at the center of the frame."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:100
msgid "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_MATRIX``"
msgstr "``V4L2_EXPOSURE_METERING_MATRIX``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:101
msgid ""
"A multi-zone metering. The light intensity is measured in several points of "
"the frame and the results are combined. The algorithm of the zones selection "
"and their significance in calculating the final value is device dependent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:108
msgid "``V4L2_CID_PAN_RELATIVE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:109
msgid ""
"This control turns the camera horizontally by the specified amount. The unit "
"is undefined. A positive value moves the camera to the right (clockwise when "
"viewed from above), a negative value to the left. A value of zero does not "
"cause motion. This is a write-only control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:115
msgid "``V4L2_CID_TILT_RELATIVE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:116
msgid ""
"This control turns the camera vertically by the specified amount. The unit "
"is undefined. A positive value moves the camera up, a negative value down. A "
"value of zero does not cause motion. This is a write-only control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:121
msgid "``V4L2_CID_PAN_RESET (button)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:122
msgid ""
"When this control is set, the camera moves horizontally to the default "
"position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:125
msgid "``V4L2_CID_TILT_RESET (button)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:126
msgid ""
"When this control is set, the camera moves vertically to the default "
"position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:129
msgid "``V4L2_CID_PAN_ABSOLUTE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:130
msgid ""
"This control turns the camera horizontally to the specified position. "
"Positive values move the camera to the right (clockwise when viewed from "
"above), negative values to the left. Drivers should interpret the values as "
"arc seconds, with valid values between -180 * 3600 and +180 * 3600 inclusive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:136
msgid "``V4L2_CID_TILT_ABSOLUTE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:137
msgid ""
"This control turns the camera vertically to the specified position. Positive "
"values move the camera up, negative values down. Drivers should interpret "
"the values as arc seconds, with valid values between -180 * 3600 and +180 * "
"3600 inclusive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:142
msgid "``V4L2_CID_FOCUS_ABSOLUTE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:143
msgid ""
"This control sets the focal point of the camera to the specified position. "
"The unit is undefined. Positive values set the focus closer to the camera, "
"negative values towards infinity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:147
msgid "``V4L2_CID_FOCUS_RELATIVE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:148
msgid ""
"This control moves the focal point of the camera by the specified amount. "
"The unit is undefined. Positive values move the focus closer to the camera, "
"negative values towards infinity. This is a write-only control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:153
msgid "``V4L2_CID_FOCUS_AUTO (boolean)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:154
msgid ""
"Enables continuous automatic focus adjustments. The effect of manual focus "
"adjustments while this feature is enabled is undefined, drivers should "
"ignore such requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:158
msgid "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_FOCUS_START (button)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:159
msgid ""
"Starts single auto focus process. The effect of setting this control when "
"``V4L2_CID_FOCUS_AUTO`` is set to ``TRUE`` (1) is undefined, drivers should "
"ignore such requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:163
msgid "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_FOCUS_STOP (button)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:164
msgid ""
"Aborts automatic focusing started with ``V4L2_CID_AUTO_FOCUS_START`` "
"control. It is effective only when the continuous autofocus is disabled, "
"that is when ``V4L2_CID_FOCUS_AUTO`` control is set to ``FALSE`` (0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:171
msgid "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS (bitmask)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:172
msgid "The automatic focus status. This is a read-only control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:174
msgid ""
"Setting ``V4L2_LOCK_FOCUS`` lock bit of the ``V4L2_CID_3A_LOCK`` control may "
"stop updates of the ``V4L2_CID_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS`` control value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:184
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS_IDLE``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:185
msgid "Automatic focus is not active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:186
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS_BUSY``"
msgstr "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS_BUSY``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:187
msgid "Automatic focusing is in progress."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:188
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS_REACHED``"
msgstr "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS_REACHED``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:189
msgid "Focus has been reached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:190
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS_FAILED``"
msgstr "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_STATUS_FAILED``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:191
msgid ""
"Automatic focus has failed, the driver will not transition from this state "
"until another action is performed by an application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:198
msgid "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE``"
msgstr "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:201
msgid "enum v4l2_auto_focus_range -"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:202
msgid "Determines auto focus distance range for which lens may be adjusted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:210
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_AUTO``"
msgstr "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_AUTO``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:211
msgid "The camera automatically selects the focus range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:212
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_NORMAL``"
msgstr "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_NORMAL``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:213
msgid "Normal distance range, limited for best automatic focus performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:215
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_MACRO``"
msgstr "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_MACRO``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:216
msgid ""
"Macro (close-up) auto focus. The camera will use its minimum possible "
"distance for auto focus."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:218
msgid "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_INFINITY``"
msgstr "``V4L2_AUTO_FOCUS_RANGE_INFINITY``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:219
msgid "The lens is set to focus on an object at infinite distance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:223
msgid "``V4L2_CID_ZOOM_ABSOLUTE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:224
msgid ""
"Specify the objective lens focal length as an absolute value. The zoom unit "
"is driver-specific and its value should be a positive integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:228
msgid "``V4L2_CID_ZOOM_RELATIVE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:229
msgid ""
"Specify the objective lens focal length relatively to the current value. "
"Positive values move the zoom lens group towards the telephoto direction, "
"negative values towards the wide-angle direction. The zoom unit is driver-"
"specific. This is a write-only control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:235
msgid "``V4L2_CID_ZOOM_CONTINUOUS (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:236
msgid ""
"Move the objective lens group at the specified speed until it reaches "
"physical device limits or until an explicit request to stop the movement. A "
"positive value moves the zoom lens group towards the telephoto direction. A "
"value of zero stops the zoom lens group movement. A negative value moves the "
"zoom lens group towards the wide-angle direction. The zoom speed unit is "
"driver-specific."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:243
msgid "``V4L2_CID_IRIS_ABSOLUTE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:244
msgid ""
"This control sets the camera's aperture to the specified value. The unit is "
"undefined. Larger values open the iris wider, smaller values close it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:248
msgid "``V4L2_CID_IRIS_RELATIVE (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:249
msgid ""
"This control modifies the camera's aperture by the specified amount. The "
"unit is undefined. Positive values open the iris one step further, negative "
"values close it one step further. This is a write-only control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:254
msgid "``V4L2_CID_PRIVACY (boolean)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:255
msgid ""
"Prevent video from being acquired by the camera. When this control is set to "
"``TRUE`` (1), no image can be captured by the camera. Common means to "
"enforce privacy are mechanical obturation of the sensor and firmware image "
"processing, but the device is not restricted to these methods. Devices that "
"implement the privacy control must support read access and may support write "
"access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:262
msgid "``V4L2_CID_BAND_STOP_FILTER (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:263
msgid ""
"Switch the band-stop filter of a camera sensor on or off, or specify its "
"strength. Such band-stop filters can be used, for example, to filter out the "
"fluorescent light component."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:269
msgid "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_N_PRESET_WHITE_BALANCE``"
msgstr "``V4L2_CID_AUTO_N_PRESET_WHITE_BALANCE``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:272
msgid "enum v4l2_auto_n_preset_white_balance -"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:273
msgid ""
"Sets white balance to automatic, manual or a preset. The presets determine "
"color temperature of the light as a hint to the camera for white balance "
"adjustments resulting in most accurate color representation. The following "
"white balance presets are listed in order of increasing color temperature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:285
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_MANUAL``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_MANUAL``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:286
msgid "Manual white balance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:287
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_AUTO``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_AUTO``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:288
msgid "Automatic white balance adjustments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:289
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_INCANDESCENT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_INCANDESCENT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:290
msgid ""
"White balance setting for incandescent (tungsten) lighting. It generally "
"cools down the colors and corresponds approximately to 2500...3500 K color "
"temperature range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:293
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_FLUORESCENT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_FLUORESCENT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:294
msgid ""
"White balance preset for fluorescent lighting. It corresponds approximately "
"to 4000...5000 K color temperature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:296
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_FLUORESCENT_H``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_FLUORESCENT_H``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:297
msgid ""
"With this setting the camera will compensate for fluorescent H lighting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:299
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_HORIZON``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_HORIZON``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:300
msgid ""
"White balance setting for horizon daylight. It corresponds approximately to "
"5000 K color temperature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:302
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_DAYLIGHT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_DAYLIGHT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:303
msgid ""
"White balance preset for daylight (with clear sky). It corresponds "
"approximately to 5000...6500 K color temperature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:305
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_FLASH``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_FLASH``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:306
msgid ""
"With this setting the camera will compensate for the flash light. It "
"slightly warms up the colors and corresponds roughly to 5000...5500 K color "
"temperature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:309
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_CLOUDY``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_CLOUDY``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:310
msgid ""
"White balance preset for moderately overcast sky. This option corresponds "
"approximately to 6500...8000 K color temperature range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:313
msgid "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_SHADE``"
msgstr "``V4L2_WHITE_BALANCE_SHADE``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:314
msgid ""
"White balance preset for shade or heavily overcast sky. It corresponds "
"approximately to 9000...10000 K color temperature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:321
msgid "``V4L2_CID_WIDE_DYNAMIC_RANGE (boolean)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:322
msgid ""
"Enables or disables the camera's wide dynamic range feature. This feature "
"allows to obtain clear images in situations where intensity of the "
"illumination varies significantly throughout the scene, i.e. there are "
"simultaneously very dark and very bright areas. It is most commonly realized "
"in cameras by combining two subsequent frames with different exposure "
"times.  [#f1]_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:331
msgid "``V4L2_CID_IMAGE_STABILIZATION (boolean)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:332
msgid "Enables or disables image stabilization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:334
msgid "``V4L2_CID_ISO_SENSITIVITY (integer menu)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:335
msgid ""
"Determines ISO equivalent of an image sensor indicating the sensor's "
"sensitivity to light. The numbers are expressed in arithmetic scale, as per :"
"ref:`iso12232` standard, where doubling the sensor sensitivity is "
"represented by doubling the numerical ISO value. Applications should "
"interpret the values as standard ISO values multiplied by 1000, e.g. control "
"value 800 stands for ISO 0.8. Drivers will usually support only a subset of "
"standard ISO values. The effect of setting this control while the "
"``V4L2_CID_ISO_SENSITIVITY_AUTO`` control is set to a value other than "
"``V4L2_CID_ISO_SENSITIVITY_MANUAL`` is undefined, drivers should ignore such "
"requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:349
#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:363
msgid "``V4L2_CID_ISO_SENSITIVITY_AUTO``"
msgstr "``V4L2_CID_ISO_SENSITIVITY_AUTO``"

