#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:370
msgid "``V4L2_CID_SCENE_MODE``"
msgstr "``V4L2_CID_SCENE_MODE``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:373
msgid "enum v4l2_scene_mode -"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:374
msgid ""
"This control allows to select scene programs as the camera automatic modes "
"optimized for common shooting scenes. Within these modes the camera "
"determines best exposure, aperture, focusing, light metering, white balance "
"and equivalent sensitivity. The controls of those parameters are influenced "
"by the scene mode control. An exact behavior in each mode is subject to the "
"camera specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:381
msgid ""
"When the scene mode feature is not used, this control should be set to "
"``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_NONE`` to make sure the other possibly related controls "
"are accessible. The following scene programs are defined:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:385
msgid "\\small"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:397
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_NONE``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_NONE``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:398
msgid "The scene mode feature is disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:399
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_BACKLIGHT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_BACKLIGHT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:400
msgid ""
"Backlight. Compensates for dark shadows when light is coming from behind a "
"subject, also by automatically turning on the flash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:402
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_BEACH_SNOW``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_BEACH_SNOW``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:403
msgid ""
"Beach and snow. This mode compensates for all-white or bright scenes, which "
"tend to look gray and low contrast, when camera's automatic exposure is "
"based on an average scene brightness. To compensate, this mode automatically "
"slightly overexposes the frames. The white balance may also be adjusted to "
"compensate for the fact that reflected snow looks bluish rather than white."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:409
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_CANDLELIGHT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_CANDLELIGHT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:410
msgid ""
"Candle light. The camera generally raises the ISO sensitivity and lowers the "
"shutter speed. This mode compensates for relatively close subject in the "
"scene. The flash is disabled in order to preserve the ambiance of the light."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:414
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_DAWN_DUSK``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_DAWN_DUSK``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:415
msgid ""
"Dawn and dusk. Preserves the colors seen in low natural light before dusk "
"and after down. The camera may turn off the flash, and automatically focus "
"at infinity. It will usually boost saturation and lower the shutter speed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:419
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_FALL_COLORS``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_FALL_COLORS``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:420
msgid ""
"Fall colors. Increases saturation and adjusts white balance for color "
"enhancement. Pictures of autumn leaves get saturated reds and yellows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:423
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_FIREWORKS``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_FIREWORKS``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:424
msgid ""
"Fireworks. Long exposure times are used to capture the expanding burst of "
"light from a firework. The camera may invoke image stabilization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:427
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_LANDSCAPE``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_LANDSCAPE``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:428
msgid ""
"Landscape. The camera may choose a small aperture to provide deep depth of "
"field and long exposure duration to help capture detail in dim light "
"conditions. The focus is fixed at infinity. Suitable for distant and wide "
"scenery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:432
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_NIGHT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_NIGHT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:433
msgid ""
"Night, also known as Night Landscape. Designed for low light conditions, it "
"preserves detail in the dark areas without blowing out bright objects. The "
"camera generally sets itself to a medium-to-high ISO sensitivity, with a "
"relatively long exposure time, and turns flash off. As such, there will be "
"increased image noise and the possibility of blurred image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:439
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_PARTY_INDOOR``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_PARTY_INDOOR``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:440
msgid ""
"Party and indoor. Designed to capture indoor scenes that are lit by indoor "
"background lighting as well as the flash. The camera usually increases ISO "
"sensitivity, and adjusts exposure for the low light conditions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:444
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_PORTRAIT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_PORTRAIT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:445
msgid ""
"Portrait. The camera adjusts the aperture so that the depth of field is "
"reduced, which helps to isolate the subject against a smooth background. "
"Most cameras recognize the presence of faces in the scene and focus on them. "
"The color hue is adjusted to enhance skin tones. The intensity of the flash "
"is often reduced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:450
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_SPORTS``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_SPORTS``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:451
msgid ""
"Sports. Significantly increases ISO and uses a fast shutter speed to freeze "
"motion of rapidly-moving subjects. Increased image noise may be seen in this "
"mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:454
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_SUNSET``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_SUNSET``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:455
msgid ""
"Sunset. Preserves deep hues seen in sunsets and sunrises. It bumps up the "
"saturation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:457
msgid "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_TEXT``"
msgstr "``V4L2_SCENE_MODE_TEXT``"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:458
msgid ""
"Text. It applies extra contrast and sharpness, it is typically a black-and-"
"white mode optimized for readability. Automatic focus may be switched to "
"close-up mode and this setting may also involve some lens-distortion "
"correction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:463
msgid "\\normalsize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:468
msgid "``V4L2_CID_3A_LOCK (bitmask)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:469
msgid ""
"This control locks or unlocks the automatic focus, exposure and white "
"balance. The automatic adjustments can be paused independently by setting "
"the corresponding lock bit to 1. The camera then retains the settings until "
"the lock bit is cleared. The following lock bits are defined:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:475
msgid ""
"When a given algorithm is not enabled, drivers should ignore requests to "
"lock it and should return no error. An example might be an application "
"setting bit ``V4L2_LOCK_WHITE_BALANCE`` when the "
"``V4L2_CID_AUTO_WHITE_BALANCE`` control is set to ``FALSE``. The value of "
"this control may be changed by exposure, white balance or focus controls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:488
msgid "``V4L2_LOCK_EXPOSURE``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:489
msgid "Automatic exposure adjustments lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:490
msgid "``V4L2_LOCK_WHITE_BALANCE``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:491
msgid "Automatic white balance adjustments lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:492
msgid "``V4L2_LOCK_FOCUS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:493
msgid "Automatic focus lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:497
msgid "``V4L2_CID_PAN_SPEED (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:498
msgid ""
"This control turns the camera horizontally at the specific speed. The unit "
"is undefined. A positive value moves the camera to the right (clockwise when "
"viewed from above), a negative value to the left. A value of zero stops the "
"motion if one is in progress and has no effect otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:504
msgid "``V4L2_CID_TILT_SPEED (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:505
msgid ""
"This control turns the camera vertically at the specified speed. The unit is "
"undefined. A positive value moves the camera up, a negative value down. A "
"value of zero stops the motion if one is in progress and has no effect "
"otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:512
msgid "``V4L2_CID_CAMERA_ORIENTATION (menu)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:513
msgid ""
"This read-only control describes the camera orientation by reporting its "
"mounting position on the device where the camera is installed. The control "
"value is constant and not modifiable by software. This control is "
"particularly meaningful for devices which have a well defined orientation, "
"such as phones, laptops and portable devices since the control is expressed "
"as a position relative to the device's intended usage orientation. For "
"example, a camera installed on the user-facing side of a phone, a tablet or "
"a laptop device is said to be have ``V4L2_CAMERA_ORIENTATION_FRONT`` "
"orientation, while a camera installed on the opposite side of the front one "
"is said to be have ``V4L2_CAMERA_ORIENTATION_BACK`` orientation. Camera "
"sensors not directly attached to the device, or attached in a way that "
"allows them to move freely, such as webcams and digital cameras, are said to "
"have the ``V4L2_CAMERA_ORIENTATION_EXTERNAL`` orientation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:534
msgid "``V4L2_CAMERA_ORIENTATION_FRONT``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:535
msgid "The camera is oriented towards the user facing side of the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:536
msgid "``V4L2_CAMERA_ORIENTATION_BACK``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:537
msgid "The camera is oriented towards the back facing side of the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:538
msgid "``V4L2_CAMERA_ORIENTATION_EXTERNAL``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:539
msgid ""
"The camera is not directly attached to the device and is freely movable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:544
msgid "``V4L2_CID_CAMERA_SENSOR_ROTATION (integer)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:545
msgid ""
"This read-only control describes the rotation correction in degrees in the "
"counter-clockwise direction to be applied to the captured images once "
"captured to memory to compensate for the camera sensor mounting rotation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:549
msgid ""
"For a precise definition of the sensor mounting rotation refer to the "
"extensive description of the 'rotation' properties in the device tree "
"bindings file 'video-interfaces.txt'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:553
msgid ""
"A few examples are below reported, using a shark swimming from left to right "
"in front of the user as the example scene to capture. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:570
msgid "Example one - Webcam"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:572
msgid ""
"Assuming you can bring your laptop with you while swimming with sharks, the "
"camera module of the laptop is installed on the user facing part of a laptop "
"screen casing, and is typically used for video calls. The captured images "
"are meant to be displayed in landscape mode (width > height) on the laptop "
"screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:578
msgid ""
"The camera is typically mounted upside-down to compensate the lens optical "
"inversion effect. In this case the value of the "
"V4L2_CID_CAMERA_SENSOR_ROTATION control is 0, no rotation is required to "
"display images correctly to the user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:583
msgid ""
"If the camera sensor is not mounted upside-down it is required to compensate "
"the lens optical inversion effect and the value of the "
"V4L2_CID_CAMERA_SENSOR_ROTATION control is 180 degrees, as images will "
"result rotated when captured to memory. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:600
msgid ""
"A software rotation correction of 180 degrees has to be applied to correctly "
"display the image on the user screen. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:615
msgid "Example two - Phone camera"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:617
msgid ""
"It is more handy to go and swim with sharks with only your mobile phone with "
"you and take pictures with the camera that is installed on the back side of "
"the device, facing away from the user. The captured images are meant to be "
"displayed in portrait mode (height > width) to match the device screen "
"orientation and the device usage orientation used when taking the picture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:623
msgid ""
"The camera sensor is typically mounted with its pixel array longer side "
"aligned to the device longer side, upside-down mounted to compensate for the "
"lens optical inversion effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:627
msgid ""
"The images once captured to memory will be rotated and the value of the "
"V4L2_CID_CAMERA_SENSOR_ROTATION will report a 90 degree rotation. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/ext-ctrls-camera.rst:643
msgid ""
"A correction of 90 degrees in counter-clockwise direction has to be applied "
"to correctly display the image in portrait mode on the device screen. ::"
msgstr ""

